[
    {
        "content": "<p>I am thinking of doing this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[vtable]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Op</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[unique]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OpVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">OPVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[vtable]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Op</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[unique]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OpVTable</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>expanding to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Op</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_IMPL</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OPVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">OPVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OpVTable</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_USE_UNIQUE_ATTR</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Op</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OpVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_IMPL</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">OpVTable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Op</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_IMPL</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_IMPL</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">VTABLE_USE_UNIQUE_ATTR</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This only needs <code>const_refs_to_static</code> feature to work (covered by project goal).<br>\nI think specifying the type name again is needed if we don't also want to use <code>associated_type_defaults</code>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"546447\">@Benno Lossin</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"690399\">@Lyude</span></p>",
        "id": 447442017,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719483828
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And this would work for all cases where <code>Foo</code> has no generics?</p>",
        "id": 447444447,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1719484741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes</p>",
        "id": 447444475,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719484753
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Seems like a good idea to me.</p>",
        "id": 447444538,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1719484785
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well actually <code>Op</code> also needs to either have no generics, or have all impl blocks specify the type</p>",
        "id": 447444569,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719484799
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So you can have <code>#[vtable] impl Op&lt;Bar&gt; for Foo</code> or <code>#[vtable] impl Op&lt;Bar&gt; for Foo&lt;Bar&gt;</code> but not <code>#[vtable] impl&lt;T&gt; Op&lt;T&gt; for Foo</code> or <code>#[vtable] impl&lt;T&gt; Op for Foo&lt;T&gt;</code>.</p>",
        "id": 447444767,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719484851
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The actual constraint is that impl block must not have generic params</p>",
        "id": 447444805,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719484870
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This seems great - let me know when you've got something working, would love to give it a shot</p>",
        "id": 447818994,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1719592719
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291566-Library/topic/Extending.20vtable.20macro.20to.20provide.20unique.20address/near/447444569\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Well actually <code>Op</code> also needs to either have no generics, or have all impl blocks specify the type</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>we should probably have a good error when one supplies generics instead of just forwarding the \"static must not depend on outer generics\" error</p>",
        "id": 447882432,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1719612826
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>syn, maybe? :)</p>",
        "id": 447890481,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719616539
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Gary, since this a static, am I right to assume that this would go into .data?</p>\n<p>Ideally, we want these function tables to be in .rodata so that they're not used by attackers to hijack execution control</p>",
        "id": 448472238,
        "sender_full_name": "Wedson Almeida Filho",
        "timestamp": 1719882761
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>AFAIK non-mut statics (with no interior mutability) already get placed in .rodata</p>",
        "id": 448510718,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1719900711
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In userspace at least non-mutable statics that contain relocations get placed in <code>.data</code> as <code>.rodata</code> is made read-only before relocations are processed. Rustc by default enables RELRO though, which places them in <code>.data.rel.ro</code> which is part of the data segment, but has an instruction for the dynamic linker to make it read-only after relocations are processed. I don't know how it works in the kernel though.</p>",
        "id": 448559643,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1719914083
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I tried to implement the macro just now and I think it'll be very hard to maintain without syn</p>",
        "id": 448584369,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1719920252
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would say to do it with <code>syn</code>, and that way we have 2 users (Benno's) and yours already for the <code>syn</code> series. I can take a look at that in a couple days.</p>",
        "id": 448585152,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1719920558
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have my WIP here: <a href=\"https://github.com/nbdd0121/linux/tree/vtable-wip\">https://github.com/nbdd0121/linux/tree/vtable-wip</a></p>",
        "id": 448835767,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1720009818
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I took <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> 's syn patches from Oct 2022 and made a few changes to make it work</p>",
        "id": 448836377,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1720009999
